responses.text:
On the scene came Christ The Lord, not with peace but with a sword;
He split the silence, rent the veil, unmasking hearts ignored.
He spoke in thunder, soft and fierce, unsettling the earth;
His word a blade, dividing bone, revealing hidden worth.

He called the meek and challenged kings, upturned tradition’s stone,
Demanded truth where lies had grown, left no soul alone.
His sword was justice, sharp and bright, to cut the chains of night;
He beckoned all to choose a side, to walk in faith and fight.

For peace that’s forged in compromise He would not gently strive;
Instead, He drew the fault lines clear, and called the dead to life.
On the scene came Christ The Lord, His presence bold and true;
Not with peace but with a sword, He called the world anew.
